<div type="definition">
<p>MOST LOW BIG SURFACE IN a PLACE on which one CAN MOVE OR STAND ETC.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The general word for the ground one stands on is dì 地, and it should be noted that most floors were clay floors. Whether the second storey floor would also be called dì 地 remains an open question.</p>
        </div>
